gw.api.match

Class MatchableKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.match.MatchableKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable

    public class MatchableKey
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable
    Wrapper around AbstractKey and is used in conjunction with the LogicalMatcher interface to provide a means of logically matching between KeyableBean:

    During construction, if the backing KeyableBean supports LogicalMatcher, it relies on the backing bean to generate the AbstractKey. If the KeyableBean is EffDated, it sets the identity set to FixedID and creates an AnonymousBeanKey. If it's a plain KeyableBean, the identity set consists of the bean's ID.
